I'm going to show you a really simple method to grow peas from seed, and this is basically 

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:24.760
using a rain-gutter here, this is just and old rain gutter so you can find hem in

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:30.120
scrap yards or anywhere really. And all you need it some compost and some soil. 

00:00:30.440 --> 00:00:36.040
Firstly you want to fill abut an inch of compost and that is going to act as a base layer

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:42.120
where all the nutrients are, then secondly every inch along we are going to plant 3 seeds

00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:49.160
along it, and then cover it with a couple of inches of  just normal soil. So lets start by filling

00:00:50.580 --> 00:00:51.940
up this rain-gutter

